.ds n) explain_acl_get_fd_or_die
.TH explain_acl_get_fd_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_acl_get_fd_or_die \- Execute \f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_acl_get_fd_or_die(3)" \
    "Execute \f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/acl_get_fd.h>
.sp 0.3
acl_t explain_acl_get_fd_or_die(int fildes);
.br
acl_t explain_acl_get_fd_on_error(int fildes);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_acl_get_fd_or_die\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) system call. On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_acl_get_fd\fP(3)
function, and then the process terminates by calling
\f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_acl_get_fd_on_error\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) system call. On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_acl_get_fd\fP(3)
function, but still returns to the caller.
.TP 8n
\f[I]fildes\fP
The fildes, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) system
call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH RETURN VALUE
The \f[B]explain_acl_get_fd_or_die\fP function only returns on success, see
\f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) for more information. On failure, prints an
explanation and exits, it does not return.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_acl_get_fd_on_error\fP function always returns the value
return by the wrapped \f[I]acl_get_fd\fP(3) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLE
The \f[B]explain_acl_get_fd_or_die\fP function is intended to be used in a
fashion similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
explain_acl_get_fd_or_die(fildes);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
